29) What is SATA?
=> SATA (Serial ATA) is a standard interface for connecting storage devices (HDD/SSD) to the motherboard. It replaced older PATA.

30) Describe the working of SATA
=> It transfers data serially over a thin cable. Supports hot-swapping in some cases; speeds: SATA II (3Gbps), SATA III (6Gbps).

