34) What is Boot Process?
 Sequence: Power on → BIOS/UEFI POST → Detect hardware → Load bootloader from storage → Load OS kernel → User login.

35) Describe the boot process in Linux?
 Similar to Windows but uses GRUB bootloader. BIOS/UEFI → GRUB menu → Load kernel → Init system (systemd) starts services → Login.

35) List out the types of display? 
=>CRT (old), LCD, LED, OLED, IPS, TN panels. Resolutions: HD, Full HD, 4K, etc. Interfaces: HDMI, DisplayPort, VGA.

36) What is printer? And type of printer?
=> A printer outputs text/images on paper. Types: Inkjet (color, home use), Laser (fast, black/white or color for offices), Dot-matrix (impact, old), 3D printers.

37) Do a practical to install the printer.
