3)	How do you troubleshoot a computer with no display on screen?
	Check power, cables (HDMI/VGA), monitor input source. 
•	Reseat GPU/RAM. 
•	Test with another monitor or integrated graphics. 
•	Check beep codes or motherboard LEDs for errors. 
•	Clear CMOS. 
•	Test PSU.


4)	You get the Blue Screen of Death (BSOD)?
=> Note error code (e.g., IRQL_NOT_LESS_OR_EQUAL). Causes: Driver issues, faulty RAM, overheating, bad updates. Fix: Update drivers, run SFC /scannow, memtest, check event viewer.

